  • A svelte, versatile camera, the silver Fujifilm X-E3 is a progression in their rangefinder-styled mirrorless series, and features an updated sensor and processor along with familiar classic design. Revolving around the 24.3MP APS-C X-Trans CMOS III sensor and X-Processor Pro image processor, high-resolution stills can be recorded with notable sharpness and clarity due to the sensor's organic layout and omission of an optical low-pass filter. Benefitting the imaging capabilities, the X-E3 retains its retro-inspired physical design complete with a high-resolution 2.36m-dot electronic viewfinder, 3.0" 1.04m-dot rear touchscreen LCD, and physical shutter speed and exposure compensation dials. Also, its wireless capabilities have been expanded to include Bluetooth connectivity for low-power image transferring and remote camera control from a linked mobile device.

item.title: Sigma 70 - 300 mm F4-5.6 DG Macro Lens Lens (Black) camera accessorires
item.dc:creator: adminvarun
item.content:encoded:
• Lens Mount: Sony Mount
  • Designed For: A68,A77 II,A99 II,
  • Lens Type: Telephoto
  • Zoom Lens
To possess a telephoto zoom lens is a prestige among your friends who just have the DSLR with the basic kit. If you want to be unique and special, then the Sigma 70-300mm F/4-5.6 DG Macro is a telephoto zoom lens specially designed to give youperfect photographic results. This compactly designed Sigma telephoto zoom lens can be used in sports and wildlife photography. The Sigma telephoto zoom lens is carefully constructed with14 elements in 10 groups. The minimum angle of view of the Sigma Macro lens is 8.2 and the maximum angle of view is 34.3. The Sigma 70-300mm F/4-5.6 DG Macro lens is specially designed for all the Sony digital single lens reflex cameras. The maximum focal length of the Sigma lens is 300 mm and the minimum focal length is 70 mm. Performance The number of diaphragm blades in the Sigma lens is 9 for high quality images. The Sigma Macro lens features a minimum aperture of F/22 - 32. Theaperture of the lens with the maximum focal length is 5.6and the aperture with the minimum focal length is 4. An aperture is a thin diaphragm which opens and closes frequently to allow light to pass through when you click a picture. This light hits the camera sensor which in turn, helps you produce images. The Sigma 70-300mm F/4-5.6 DG Macro lens is ideal for portrait photography. Thelens measures 76.6 mm x 119.5 mmin diameter and length. However, the length of the lens when it is extended is 208.3 mm. This size of the Sigma lens makes it convenient for you to fit the lens easily in your camera bag, making space for other camera accessories. The Sigma macro lens weighs just 530 g for easy portability. Features The maximum magnification of the Sigma 70-300mm F/4-5.6 DG Macro lens is 1: 4 x. This allows you to closely capture the expressions of your loved ones. Thefilter attachment size of the Sigma lens is 58 mm. This is the front end of the lens which lets you attach different kind of filters to your lens. According to your requirement, you can attach any filter that is available in the market. You can fill your frame with a lot of things and attach the filter which suits the situation in your frame. You can use a dark coloured filter if you have to create a night effect in your picture. Theclosest focusing distance of the Sigma telephoto zoom lens is 1.5 mby which you can capture the right moment at the right time to add them to your archives. The Sigma 70-300mm F/4-5.6 DG Macro lens is an appropriate choice to capture scenic details and even groups of flowers.
